article.headline: S. Dakota St. 84, Arkansas St. 78
article.story: BROOKINGS, S.D. (AP) -- Michael Loney scored all 16 of his points in the second half and grabbed 11 rebounds to help South Dakota State end a six-game losing streak with an 84-78 win over Arkansas State on Monday night. Matt Cadwell scored 23 points, five in the last minute, as the Jackrabbits (1-6) fought off the Indians (4-4) to pick up their first victory of the season. Cadwell's basket with 50 seconds left gave San Diego State an 81-78 lead. With 28 seconds to play, Arkansas State's Ryan Wedel made a 3-pointer that would have tied it, but the shot was disallowed as it came moments after Indians' coach Brian Boyer called a timeout. The Indians missed a 3-pointer after the timeout. With 10 seconds remaining, Cadwell made one of two free throws, and Andy Kleinjan closed out the scoring with a free throw with two seconds to play. Kleinjan finished with 12 points. Isaac Wells scored 18 points to lead Arkansas State. Yual Banks added 16 points and Chris Brown 12.
